summary:
Capital Raising Announcement:
- Structure: Renounceable rights issue ($9m) + Placement to Amari Metals Australia Pty Ltd (minimum $6m, up to $15m total).
- Total Capital Raised: Minimum A$15m, maximum A$24m at A$0.03/share.
- Key Condition: Amari to own 51% post-completion.
- Timetable: Shareholder meeting expected late August 2025; documentation sent early August.

New Loan Facility:
- Terms: 3-year facility, same pricing as current, with current facilities extended to 30 September 2025.

Material Conditions:
- Cross-completion of capital raise and loan agreements.
- Shareholder and regulatory approvals required.

Governance Change:
- Amari to appoint Stephen Robertson as non-independent director post-transaction.

Note: Boilerplate/forward-looking statements omitted.

June Quarter FY 2026 Investor Update – Material Information

Key Highlights:

  • Combogesic IV® launched in Canada – First sales under AFT’s Canadian subsidiary, targeting the non-opioid pain management market amid Canada’s opioid crisis.
  • Extended US licensing agreement with Hikma Pharmaceuticals – Covers both Combogesic IV (IV form) and Combogesic Rapid (tablet form) for broader US commercialisation; restructured profit-sharing model.
  • R&D Pipeline Progress:
  • Antibiotic eyedrop – Pre-IND filed with FDA; IND targeted before year-end.
  • Strawberry Birthmarks topical treatment – Pre-IND filing expected this year.
  • Novel injectable iron – IND filing planned by year-end.
  • New project – Improved formulation targeting a US$180M niche market, expected FY27 filing.
  • Pediatric Maxigesic IV study – Prep underway to expand label into pediatric pain management.
  • Global expansion – Canada joins existing operations in Singapore, Hong Kong, South Africa, US, EU, and UK; further OTC and in-licensed product launches planned for FY26.

No financial or capital structure updates disclosed.

Understood. Please upload or provide the text of the ASX announcement PDF, and I will analyze it strictly based on your guidelines, extracting only material information relevant for trading or capital markets decisions.

Quarterly Report (Appendix 4C)
- Cash Balance: AUD $15M (vs. AUD $20M prior quarter).
- Highlights: Production up 10% QoQ; costs down 5%.

Capital Structure Update

  • Redemption of CIP1 Equity Securities: 85,341,018 unquoted securities redeemed at NZ$1.00 each (total NZ$85.3M).
  • Cancellation of CIP1 Warrants: 7,561,881 unquoted warrants cancelled at nil consideration.
  • Debt Repayment: NZ$85.3M of unquoted CIP1 debt securities repaid.
  • Impact on Outstanding Securities:
  • Remaining CIP1 Equity Securities: 376,711,053 (unquoted).
  • Remaining CIP1 Warrants: 9,903,147 (unquoted).
  • Reason: Dividends became payable on portion of CIP1 Equity Securities; warrants’ exercise period expired.

Note: No material liquidity or trading impact (securities unquoted).

• Dividend Details:
  • Final dividend of NZD 0.1325 per share (AUD 0.1229 equivalent), unfranked.

  • Ex-date: 11/6/2025; Record date: 12/6/2025; Payment date: 2/7/2025.

  • Dividend Reinvestment Plan (DRP):

  • Strike price set at NZD 10.42983548 per share (2% discount).
  • DRP election deadline: 13/6/2025 15:00 NZ time.

  • New shares issued under DRP rank pari passu.

  • Tax: 15% withholding tax applies; no franking.

No other material information identified.
